HEADWORD: Eclogite
<hw>Ec"lo*gite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Ecloque</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A rock consisting of
granular red garnet, light green smaragdite, and common hornblende; --
so called in reference to its beauty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eclogue</ent>⟦br⟧
